						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Tribhuvanamalla Sōvidēva A.D. 1170.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers to Tribhuvanamalla Sōvidēva. It is dated in Śaka 1093, Vi[kṛiti], Kārttika śu. 5, Thursday, corresponding regularly to A.D. 1170, October 15, f.d.t. 19. The Śaka year was current. It records a gift for the offerings <hi rend="italic">etc.,</hi> of the god Taṭēśvara by the king's officer Sōvaṇa and <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Kattamadēva who went to the place in person.</p>						

						</summary>
